:''See also'' '''[[fornax]]'''

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille. Originally called ''[[fornax|Fornax]] [[chemica|Chemica]]'', 
{{L.}} for "[[chemical]] [[furnace]]".

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Fornax}}
'''Fornax'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[winter]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[furnace]]. It lies near the constellation [[Eridanus]].
#{{astronomy}}: A dwarf [[galaxy]] located in the constellation Fornax.
#{{greekmyth}}: The [[Roman]] [[goddess]] of [[oven]]s.

